<article>
    <h1>Sav&#xAD;ing Spa&#xAD;ces Open Call Open Call: Sit With Me FAL Po&#xAD;etry (Com&#xAD;pe&#xAD;ti&#xAD;tion)</h1>
    <h2></h2>
    <section>
        <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/textview" title="The Straits Times">The Straits Times</a>
        - <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/20200911/textview" title="The Straits Times - 2020-09-11"><time>2020-09-11</time></a>
        - <span>LIFE</span>
        - <span role="byline"></span>
    </section>

    <p>Sav­ing Spa­ces is a project that aims to pro­duce a po­si­tion paper on the im­por­tance of the ex­is­tence and preser­va­tion of art spa­ces in Singapore. Through this open call, it would like to know how the NTU Cen­tre for Con­tem­po­rary Art Singapore, Cen­tre 42, The Nec­es­sary Stage, The Sub­sta­tion and In­ter­cul­tural The­atre In­sti­tute, or other lost or en­dan­gered arts spa­ces, have been mean­ing­ful to you. You can sub­mit per­sonal anec­dotes and sto­ries about these spa­ces and/or cre­ative re­sponses to them in any</p>
    <p>INFO:</p>
    <p>The Tapestry Project SG is to be com­mis­sioned by the Na­tional Arts Coun­cil to present the pro­gramme</p>
    <p>Sit With Me at this year’s Singapore Writ­ers Fes­ti­val. It is look­ing for writ­ers who share pas­sion for the lit­er­ary arts and men­tal health­care, and aims to cu­rate up to 12 sto­ries – prose or po­etry – for Sit With Me.</p>
    <p>Each story should be ac­com­pa­nied by a pho­to­graph of a chair or seat that is rel­e­vant to the story, as well as au­dio and video el­e­ments for a more im­mer­sive ex­pe­ri­ence. Where rel­e­vant, the cu­rated sto­ries will be paired with pub­lished works to show the par­al­lels be­tween lo­cal sto­ries and other lit­er­ary works. There will be mone­tary com­pen­sa­tion for se­lected sto­ries.</p>
    <p>WHEN: Sub­mit by Sept 20</p>
    <p>INFO: bit.ly/33cx1Q7</p>
    <p>Project Feed-A-Lot (FAL) is a so­cial ini­tia­tive pi­o­neered by youth vol­un­teers from Citi-YMCA Youth</p>
    <p>For Causes and West Coast CC to help raise funds for Singapore’s food-in­se­cure pop­u­la­tion. The po­etry com­pe­ti­tion aims to raise aware­ness of food in­se­cu­rity. Three cash prizes are up for grabs, with an ad­di­tional spe­cial prize for par­tic­i­pants aged seven to 12.</p>
    <p>WHEN: Sub­mit on­line by Sept 25</p>
    <p>INFO: art­sre­pub­lic.sg</p>


</article>

